17/12/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonian police announced on Friday (December 15th) that three Bulgarian nationals were detained while attempting to export weaponry to Bulgaria.
Three trucks loaded with arms -- which were reportedly presented as an old decommissioned equipment of the Macedonian army but actually included new equipment were seized outside Skopje.
The Ministries of Interior and Defence have opened separate probes into the issue.
(Dnevnik, Makfax, A1 TV, Telma TV - 16/12/06)
